<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h1><a name="Xrootd_RPM_Phase_1_Requirements"></a> Xrootd RPM Phase 1 Requirements </h1>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Packages_needed"></a> Packages needed </span></h2> <ul>
<li> xrootd-server 
</li> <li> xrootd-client 
</li> <li> xrootdfs
</li> <li> GridFTP with xrootd DSI plugin
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Platforms"></a> Platforms </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Scientific Linux 5
</li> <li> 64 bit
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Details"></a> Details </span></h2>
<p /> <ol>
<li> Xrootd should be provided as an RPM. (And therefore it's okay to install as root.)
</li> <li> The xrootd daemons should run as the xrootd user. 
</li> <li> ATLAS system administrators need to be able to configure their system such that they can provide a non-root user with the ability to start and stop the xrootd processes and change configuration files. 
</li> <li> The RPM should be installed in FHS locations.
</li> <li> The package should support all of Xrootd's authentication methods. However, if it's significant effort to support Kerberos, it can be dropped.
</li> <li> Upon completion of the RPM installation, the client should be able to copy and retrieve file accessing node directly.
</li> <li> The start and stop scripts and configuration of the following daemons should be available on each xrootd node: <ol>
<li type="A"> xrootd <ul>
<li> xrootd data server
</li> <li> xrootd daemon for server side inventory
</li></ul> 
</li> <li type="A"> cmsd
</li> <li type="A"> frm   <ul>
<li> purge daemon
</li> <li> copy daemon
</li></ul> 
</li> <li type="A"> xrootdfs  <ul>
<li>  xrootdfs should be able start one or more mount points; each corresponding to a unique redirector or stand alone dataserver
</li> <li>  Once xrootdfs has been modified to be started and stopped using the Linux mount command, it should be used instead of /etc/init.d scripts
</li></ul> 
</li></ol> 
</li> <li>  rpm used to install xrootdfs binary should include dependancies for all fuse repositories
</li></ol> 
<p />
<p />
  Details on the Baseline configuration for a US ATLAS Tier 3g  can be found here:  <a href="https://atlaswww.hep.anl.gov/twiki/bin/view/UsAtlasTier3/ClusterElements" target="_top">US ATLAS Tier 3g description</a> </div><!-- /patternTopic-->
<p />
